This paper deals with interference management in wireless communication, which is a topic that falls under the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of coding schemes and capacity analysis, which are relevant to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of superposition schemes, which are commonly used in Multimedia (cs.MM) and Computer Engineering (cs.CE) applications.
